      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those who praise the UN's humanitarian work are focusing on its secondary functions rather than its primary mandate of preventing war. While aid is valuable, it is a palliative measure, not a preventative solution to conflict. The legal frameworks are merely aspirational documents that powerful nations routinely ignore when their strategic interests are at stake. Therefore, calling it effective is a deliberate misreading of its core political failures.",
      "source": "target",
